Package org.opengis.wrapper.netcdf

Class NetcdfMetadata

  • Object
    • NetcdfMetadata
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Address, Citation, CitationDate, OnlineResource, Extent, GeographicBoundingBox, GeographicExtent, DataIdentification, Identification, Identifier, Metadata
    public class NetcdfMetadata
extends Object
implements Metadata, DataIdentification, Identifier, Citation, CitationDate, OnlineResource, Address, Extent, GeographicBoundingBox
    A Metadata implementation backed by a netCDF NetcdfFile object. All getter methods fetch their values from the netCDF file, so change to the netCDF file content will be immediately reflected in this class.

    Unless otherwise noted in the javadoc, this implementation defines a one-to-one relationship between the metadata attributes and netCDF attributes. This simple model allows us to implement relevant interfaces in a single class. Note that this simplification may not be appropriate for real world usages — the purpose of this class is mainly to provide a starting point for your own implementations.

    Some interfaces implemented by this class or its component objects:

    • Metadata is the root interface.
    • Identifier implements the value returned by Citation.getIdentifiers().
      • NetCDF attributes: id, naming_authority.
    • DataIdentification implements the value returned by Metadata.getIdentificationInfo().
      • NetCDF attributes: summary, purpose, topic_category, cdm_data_type, comment, acknowledgment.
    • CitationDate implements the value returned by Metadata.getDateInfo().
      • NetCDF attributes: metadata_creation.
    • Citation implements the value returned by Identification.getCitation(), which contain only the creator. This simple implementation ignores the publisher and contributors.
      • NetCDF attributes: title.
    • Responsibility implements the value returned by Citation.getCitedResponsibleParties(), which contain only the creator and the institution.
      • NetCDF attributes: creator_name, institution.
    • Individual implements the value returned by Responsibility.getParties(), which contain only the creator. This simple implementation ignores the publisher and contributors.
      • NetCDF attributes: creator_name.
    • Address implements the value returned by Contact.getAddress().
      • NetCDF attributes: creator_email.
    • GeographicBoundingBox implements the value returned by Extent.getGeographicElements().
      • NetCDF attributes: geospatial_lon_min, geospatial_lon_max, geospatial_lat_min, geospatial_lat_max.

    Javadoc convention: all public non-deprecated methods in this class can be grouped in 3 categories, identifiable by the first words in their Javadoc:

    • Each method documented as “Returns foo…” maps directly to a netCDF attribute or hard-coded non-empty value.
    • Each method documented as “Encapsulates foo…” returns an object (often this) providing the getter methods for a group of attributes. This encapsulation is done for compliance with the ISO 19115 model.
    • Each method documented as “Default to foo…” is an unimplemented property.
    Since:
    3.1
    See Also:
    NetCDF Attribute Convention for Dataset Discovery

      • getContacts

        public Collection<? extends ResponsibleParty> getContacts()
        Defaults to a synonymous for the point of contacts in this simple implementation. Note that in theory, those two methods are not strictly synonymous since getContacts() shall return the contact for the metadata, while getPointOfContacts() shall return the contact for the data. However the attributes in netCDF files usually don't make this distinction.
        Specified by:
